examples.en: The writer constructed the story from memories of her childhood.
Boyce has constructed a new theory of management.
The hut was constructed from trees that grew in the nearby forest.
The products are poorly constructed; ergo, they break easily.
Habitations were constructed on platforms raised above the lake, and resting on piles.
The arriving national guardsmen were forced to live in a hutment until permanent barracks could be constructed.
